{"title_page": "Bello FiGo", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Italian internet personality}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name = Bello FiGo\n| image = Bello Figo Gu.jpg\n| caption = \n| birth_name = Paul Yeboah\n| channel_name = TheGucciboy1992\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1992|8|2|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Accra]], Ghana\n| nationality = {{flatlist|\n| family = Matteo Salvini + Alessandra Mussolini\n* [[Ghanaians|Ghanaian]]\n* American \n* Italian\n}}\n| partner =\n| residence = [[Parma]], Emilia-Romagna, Italy\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n* [[Internet personality]]\n* Singer\n}}\n| website = {{URL|www.youtube.com/user/TheGucciboy1992}}\n| pseudonym = BelloFiGo, BelloFiGo Gu\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* [[comedy music]]\n* [[parody music]]\n}}\n| subscribers = \n| subscriber_date = \n| views = \n| view_date = \n| network = \n| associated_acts = \n}}\n\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name =Paul Yeboah\n|image =\n|caption =\n|background = solo_singer\n|birth_date = 4 August 1992\n|death_date = \n|origin = [[Accra]], Ghana\n|genre= [[comedy music]]\n|genre2 = [[parody music]]\n|genre3 = \n|years_active = 2010\u2013present\n|website = {{URL|www.youtube.com/user/TheGucciboy1992}}\n}}\n'''Paul Yeboah''' (born 4 August 1992), known online by his nicknames  '''Bello FiGo''' and '''Bello FiGo Gu''' and in the past also as '''Bello FiGo Gucci''', is a Ghanaian and naturalized Italian, and he also declared to have the American citizenship<ref>https://www.ilgiornale.it/news/cronache/bello-figo-dio-mi-ha-mandato-qui-cantare-1352379.html</ref>, [[internet personality]], [[YouTuber]] and singer known in Italy for his numerous songs in which he often parodies different topics like racism, sexism and politics that often caused controversy and debate in Italy about his social, political and cultural role because of the way he talks about these topics.\n\n==Life and career==\nBorn in [[Accra]], Bello FiGo moved to Italy in [[Parma]] with his family in 2004.<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|url=http://www.corriere.it/cronache/17_gennaio_15/bello-figo-rap-se-canti-qui-finisci-ospedale-concerti-negati-bello-figo-rapper-immigrato-4758b044-da9e-11e6-817c-c522bb7cbdb6.shtml|title=\"Se canti qui finisci in ospedale\" I tre concerti negati a Bello Figo, il rapper immigrato dal Ghana|first=Alessandro|last=Fulloni|date=14 January 2017|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref> In 2010 he started to publish self-produced music videos on his own YouTube channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.soundsblog.it/post/463437/bello-figo-chi-e|title=Bello Figo, chi \u00e8 il rapper che sta facendo impazzire il web (e Alessandra Mussolini)?|date=3 December 2016|website=Soundsblog.it}}</ref> In a first moment he used the nicknames Bello FiGo Gucci and Gucci Boy but the popularity of his videos caused that when people searched \"Gucci\" in Italian web search engines the first search engine results were about him instead of the Italian brand of fashion [[Gucci]]. This caused him to be sued by the company, then withdrawn following a consensual agreement with which Bello FiGo renounced the use of the name Gucci.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.giornaledibrescia.it/tempo-libero/bello-figo-voi-ridete-io-faccio-milioni-di-view-1.1836898|title=Bello Figo: \"Voi ridete, io faccio milioni... di view\"|date=6 March 2014|website=Giornale di brescia}}</ref>\n\nBello FiGo's songs are done in an intentionally poor style called \"trash rap\" because of the low technical-stylistic quality of his rap music accompanied by bizarre, surreal, satirical and often grammatically incorrect texts.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilfoglio.it/musica/2016/11/30/news/bello-figo-rapper-intellettuale-trash-108502/|title=Ascoltare Bello FiGo per capire i tic della politica (e il referendum)|website=Il Foglio}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.corriere.it/spettacoli/16_dicembre_06/fraintendimento-testi-satirici-rapper-ghanese-bello-figo-72485258-bb24-11e6-8d3b-c05118807aea.shtml|title=Il fraintendimento dei testi satirici del rapper ghanese Bello FiGo|first=Aldo|last=Grasso|date=12 May 2016|website=Corriere della Sera}}</ref> His music videos, published only on YouTube, have totaled millions of views (for example, the song \"Non Pago Affitto\" has as of January 2020 over 25 millions views)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ookGv44MMd4|title=Bello FiGo ft The GynoZz \u2013 Non Pago Affitto (SwaG NeGri) Stai Li A Pagare!!! ASSGARAA|last=Bello FiGo|date=23 October 2016|via=YouTube}}</ref> and have made Bello FiGo a phenomenon of the Internet in Italy.\n\nAfter the first songs, characterized mainly by topics of vulgarity and sexism, Bello FiGo took over from 2016, with the songs \"Sono bello come profugo\", \"Non Pago Affitto\" and \"Referendum Costituzionale\", a more political role, applying his style and its self-irony to the stereotypical arguments inherent in immigrants in Italy, described as being mostly nasty and delinquent. He also mocked, besides these stereotypes, various political figures. For this reason in 2016 he was defined by [[Rolling Stone]] music magazine as \"the most politicized artist in Italy\",<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.it/musica/news-musica/bello-figo-e-lartista-piu-politicizzato-in-italia/340465/|title=Bello Figo \u00e8 l'artista pi\u00f9 politicizzato in Italia|date=22 November 2016}}</ref> and between the end of 2016 and the beginning of 2017, it suffered several disputes and threats of violence, even of racist background, by groups and subjects close to the extreme right, that led to the cancellation of some of his concerts for fear of public tensions and disorders (in [[Brescia]], in [[Borgo Virgilio]], in [[Legnano]] and in Rome).<ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.internazionale.it/opinione/christian-raimo/2017/02/01/bello-figo-rapper-razzismo | title=Il rapper Bello FiGo sfida i nostri stereotipi sull'immigrazione| date=February 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.vice.com/it/article/bello-figo-gu-chi-e-analisi | title=Una mattina mi son svegliato / O Bello Fi, Bello Fi, Bello Figo Gu| date=18 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://milano.corriere.it/notizie/cronaca/16_dicembre_27/minacce-morte-rapper-bello-figo-mantova-5c84c44a-cbac-11e6-8b9b-1b0efa3fb5ec.shtml | title=Minacce di morte al rapper Bello Figo Annullato il concerto di Capodanno| date=27 December 2016}}</ref> \nOn 30 April 2018 he published [[Swag negro. Non ce la fa nessuno]], an [[autobiography|autobiographical book]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.googleadservices.com/pagead/aclk?sa=L&ai=DChcSEwiL5-KA_tnfAhXCQ9MKHZ40DXkYABAAGgJ3Yg&ohost=www.google.it&cid=CAASE-RoTkgdSWALH2XsG5k82bzQNTs&sig=AOD64_3O0UGbDK7oUlm-1tS4xp8fPSh7AQ&q=&ved=2ahUKEwi-ld2A_tnfAhUuM-wKHcLDAR4Q0Qx6BAgGEAE&adurl=|title=Amazon.it: bello figo swag negro|website=googleadservices.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.ibs.it/swag-negro-non-ce-fa-libro-bello-figo/e/9788817101875 | title=Swag negro. Non ce la fa nessuno \u2013 Bello Figo \u2013 Libro \u2013 Rizzoli \u2013 Varia &#124; IBS}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.booktobook.it/libri/bello-figo/ | title=Bello Figo: Cosa aspettarsi dal suo primo libro, Swag Negro| date=8 May 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=http://www.lafeltrinelli.it/libri/bello-figo/swag-negro-non-ce-fa/9788817101875 | title=Libro Swag negro. Non ce la fa nessuno \u2013 Bello Figo \u2013 Rizzoli \u2013 Varia &#124; LaFeltrinelli}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://it.blastingnews.com/cultura-spettacoli/2018/05/swag-negro-non-ce-la-fa-nessuno-il-nuovo-libro-di-bello-figo-002554067.html | title='Swag Negro, non-ce la fa nessuno', il nuovo libro di Bello Figo| date=6 May 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn December 2019 Bello FiGo was denounced by the [[University of Pisa]] and its rector, Paolo Mancarella, that declared, after being contacted by the [[Agenzia Giornalistica Italia|AGI]], that the University would have done everything to defend its honour and reputation, because of a song about sex Bello FiGo has published on his official YouTube channel on 6 December 2019, \"Trombo a facolt\u00e0\", that was recorded inside the classes of economics of the University, which declared that its staff didn't know anything about it and didn't give its authorization to record the video.<ref>https://www.rollingstone.it/musica/news-musica/bello-figo-denunciato-dalluniversita-di-pisa-per-il-video-di-trombo-a-facolta/491586/</ref><ref>https://www.iltempo.it/cronache/2019/12/11/news/bello-figo-trombo-a-facolta-video-hot-universita-pisa-denuncia-modelle-1254077/</ref><ref>https://voxnews.info/2019/12/11/trombo-a-facolta-bello-figo-gira-video-sconcio-alluniversita-di-pisa/</ref>\nIn February 2020 he released the song \"CoronaVirus\" that got more than 4.5 milion views on YouTube.\n== References ==\n<!-- Inline citations added to your article will automatically display here. See https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/WP:REFB for instructions on how to add citations. -->\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:FiGo, Bello}}\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian internet celebrities]]\n[[Category:Italian YouTubers]]\n[[Category:Ghanaian emigrants to Italy]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{short description|Italian internet personality}}\n{{Infobox YouTube personality\n| name = Bello FiGo\n| image = Bello Figo Gu.jpg\n| caption = \n| birth_name = Paul Yeboah\n| channel_name = TheGucciboy1992\n| birth_date  = {{birth date and age|1992|8|2|df=yes}}\n| birth_place = [[Accra]], Ghana\n| nationality = {{flatlist|\n* [[Ghanaians|Ghanaian]]\n* American \n* Italian\n}}\n| partner =\n| residence = [[Parma]], Emilia-Romagna, Italy\n| occupation = {{flatlist|\n* [[Internet personality]]\n* Singer\n}}\n| website = {{URL|www.youtube.com/user/TheGucciboy1992}}\n| pseudonym = BelloFiGo, BelloFiGo Gu\n| years_active = 2010\u2013present\n| genre = {{flatlist|\n* 